<section id="tasks_creating_new_server">
	<title>Creating a new LDAP server</title>
	<para>
		To create a new LDAP server, in the Servers view toolbar, click on
		the
		<imageobject>
			<imagedata scale="50"
				fileref="images/icons_server_new.png" format="PNG" />
		</imageobject>
		<emphasis role="strong">New Server</emphasis>
		button, or use the
		<emphasis role="strong">Strg-E</emphasis>
		shortcut.
	</para>
	<para>The following wizard appears:</para>
	<para>
		<screenshot>
			<mediaobject>
				<imageobject>
					<imagedata scale="50"
						fileref="images/tasks_new_server_wizard.png" format="PNG" />
				</imageobject>
			</mediaobject>
		</screenshot>
	</para>
	<para>Give a name to the server.</para>
	<para>
		<informaltable frame="all">
			<tgroup cols="3">
				<colspec colname="Option" colwidth="1*" />
				<colspec colname="Description" colwidth="2*" />
				<colspec colname="Default" colwidth="1*" />
				<thead>
					<row>
						<entry>Option</entry>
						<entry>Description</entry>
						<entry>Default</entry>
					</row>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<row>
						<entry>Server Type</entry>
						<entry>
							The type of the LDAP server. Currently only the
							Apache Directory Server (ApacheDS) is available.
						</entry>
						<entry>empty</entry>
					</row>
					<row>
						<entry>Server Name</entry>
						<entry>
							The name of the LDAP server. In the LDAP Servers
							view the server is listed with this name. The
							name must be unique.
						</entry>
						<entry>empty</entry>
					</row>
				</tbody>
			</tgroup>
		</informaltable>
	</para>
</section>